Author: ricebowlbitch
Text: i’m sorry to validate the reality that you’re hesitant to confront, but this is definitely disordered behavior and you absolutely should ask for help. you’re not overreacting and none of those behaviors are normal. binge-restrict cycles aren’t normal, being afraid to eat in front of others isn’t normal, only feeling attractive when you’re starving isn’t normal. i’m sorry :(  i guess those things are all pretty normal on this sub since we’re all kinda fucked up (no offense guys i love u all) but you could definitely benefit from getting professional help. i hope you do seek out a therapist and manage to stop your binge/restrict cycle, i know how awful and endless they can feel. good luck <3
